RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALPINE MIST was unhurried around the first turn then made a rail bid on the backstretch and through the final turn, moved out to three wide at the sixteenths pole and made a rebid to clear late. WHERE'S AUNT J sprinted to a clear lead to set most of the pace from the inside to the top of the stretch then was headed at the eighth pole and battled with ADDI BUG in the stretch and was out finished. ADDI BUG tracked the leaders from the two path through the final turn then engaged the leader at the eighth pole and dueled in the stretch with WHERE'S AUNT J but was outkicked. TAKEN IT was forwardly placed in the two path through the first turn, made a bid at the three eighths pole, moved out to three wide in upper stretch and finished evenly. LOUISIANA LIBERTY was allowed to settle around the first turn then moved out to four wide at the five sixteenths pole to make a mild bid and flattened out. DECORATED LADY stalked the pace from the two path to the five sixteenths pole and stopped.
